            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "2-HE-3",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.999
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Pure He-3 was transferred from the",
                "glass vessel, in which it was supplied at 0.8 atm, by",
                "a simple flow inducer to attain a final pressure of",
                "4 atm in the target cell. Gas cell consisted of a dural",
                "cylinder of outer diam 7.7 cm and inner diam 5.2 cm",
                "into which four windows were cut so that the upper and",
                "lower parts of the cylinder were connected by four",
                "struts. The thickness of the target and solid angle for",
                "detection of the scattered protons was defined by two",
                "collimator slits on each telescope arm. All four",
                "collimators were approximately 2.4 mm wide by 9 mm high"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " two semiconductor telescopes were",
                "used, a charge-one telescope for detecting protons,",
                "deuterons or tritons and a charge-two telescope for",
                "detecting 3He and 4He particles. The charge-one",
                "telescope consisted of a 0.5 mm thick silicon surface",
                "barrier dE detector and a 5.0 mm lithium-drifted",
                "silicon E-detector, while the charge-two telescope",
                "consisted of a 0.1 mm dE detector and a 1.5 mm",
                "E-detector, both of which were silicon surface",
                "barrier counters."
              ]
            }
          ],
